======================================================================
H_3 STRUCTURAL ANALYSIS
======================================================================

  At n=6, H_3(T,T\v) = 1 occurs 1920 times.
  Two structural types based on dim(R_3):
    Type 1: dim(R_3)=6, ker=1, im=0 — 480 cases
    Type 2: dim(R_3)=14, ker=6, im=5 — 1440 cases
  Total: 1920 = 320 × 6 (i.e., 320 tournaments × 6 vertices)
  But from good_vertex: all have beta_3(T\v)=0 for ALL v
  So H_3(T,T\v) = beta_3(T) for these. All 320 have beta_3=1.
  1920 = 320 × 6 confirms: H_3=1 for ALL vertex pairs of beta_3=1 tournaments.

  KEY INSIGHT: For beta_3=1 tournaments, H_3(T,T\v) = 1 for ALL v.
  This means beta_3(T) = H_3(T,T\v) + rank(i_*) = 1 + 0 = 1
  where rank(i_*) = 0 because beta_3(T\v) = 0.
  Consistent with the exact equation.

